  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nCurrently, FC plugin returns volume name and empty FCVolumeSource during ConstrutVolumeSpec during `filesystem volume's reconstruction`. However, in order to recreate newMounter from volumeSpec, volume information are lacking. As a result, filesystem volume's reconstruction always fails.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nFilesystem volume's reconstruction works properly, then a volume is unmounted and detached from kubelet node.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n(1) Create filesystem volume using FC plugin\r\n(2) Restart kubelet service which a pod with FC volume is running\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\ncc @rootfs @jsafrane \r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n```\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10+\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.0-alpha.1.568+df2428c6dd30c5-dirty\", GitCommit:\"df2428c6dd30c591444c9bd9b5e8322986da331a\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2018-01-10T00:24:57Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.2\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"10+\", GitVersion:\"v1.10.0-alpha.1.568+df2428c6dd30c5-dirty\", GitCommit:\"df2428c6dd30c591444c9bd9b5e8322986da331a\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2018-01-10T01:10:36Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.2\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\n- Install tools: local-cluster-up.sh\r\n",
